(30, 'International Journal of Broadcasting and Communications Technology', 'Inactive', '2023-07-17 10:12:58', '2023-11-17 11:40:54', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The International Journal of Broadcasting and Communication Technology (IJBCT) is a scholarly and interdisciplinary publication produced by the Department of Broadcasting at the School of Communication, Lagos State University. The journal is released twice per year, though its frequency may increase if the editorial board determines that resources are available to support such a change.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">IJBCT is available to readers in both print and online formats. All articles undergo rigorous peer review by at least two assessors, with book and film submissions reviewed by one. The journal evaluates each submission based on its individual merit and contribution to knowledge, irrespective of the author\'s gender, ideology, race, or ethnicity. As an equal opportunity journal, IJBCT values inclusivity and diversity.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Authors of successful submissions may be required to provide a stipend to support publication costs, but in return, they will receive two copies of the edition in which their work is featured. Overall, IJBCT is a reputable and inclusive journal that values quality, accessibility, and diversity in publishing.</p>', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">International Journal of Broadcasting and Communication Technology (IJBCT) is a scholarly and interdisciplinary publication of the Department of Broadcasting, School of Communication, Lagos State University.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">It is devoted to scholarly research and professional discourse among media educators and practitioners particularly in fields such as Broadcasting, Film/Video, Marketing Distribution and Consumption, Communication Technology ICT, Telephony and Telecommunications Journalism, Community Communication, Political Communication, Measurement and Regulation/Deregulation.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Well-researched articles detailing quantitative and/or qualitative methods, critical analysis and occasional book/film, reviews are particularly desired.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Dedicated editions may occasionally be published where a guest editor may be appointed as the coordinator of such a special edition.</p>', '<p><strong>Professor Andrew A. Moemeka</strong>, University of Connecticut, USA<br><strong>Professor Abiodun S. Salawu</strong>,<strong> </strong>NorthZWest University, South Africa<br><strong>Dr J.O Akin Sofoluwe, </strong>Chrisland University, Abeokuta<br><strong>Professor Rotimi W. Olatunji</strong>, Lagos State University<br><strong>Dr Jimi Kayode</strong>,<strong> </strong>Lagos State University<br><strong>Dr Babalola T. Isiaka</strong>, AOCOED<br><strong>Prof. Yinka Alawode</strong>, Lagos State University<br><strong>Secretary and Business Manager</strong>, Lanre Biobaku, Lagos State University</p>', '<p>For&nbsp;<a class=\"MarkdownLink_linkifiedLink__KxC9G\">scholarly research articles</a>&nbsp;submitted to the&nbsp;<a class=\"MarkdownLink_linkifiedLink__KxC9G\">International Journal of Broadcasting</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a class=\"MarkdownLink_linkifiedLink__KxC9G\">Communication Technology</a> (IJBCT), the maximum length is 15 pages, with A4 double-line spacing. Authors should prepare their references in accordance with the latest edition of the American Psychologist Association (APA) Publication Manual.</p>\r\n<p>To submit an article to&nbsp;<a class=\"MarkdownLink_linkifiedLink__KxC9G\">IJBCT</a>, authors can use the&nbsp;<a class=\"MarkdownLink_linkifiedLink__KxC9G\">submission portal</a> provided on this website. By following these guidelines, authors can help ensure their research will be considered for publication in the IJBCT journal.</p>', '<p>Open Access</p>', 29, '2141-1883', NULL, NULL),
(31, 'Media and Communication Review', 'Active', '2023-10-06 17:07:32', '2023-11-17 12:31:43', NULL, '<p>Media and Communication Review (MCR) is a bi-annual, online and off-line Journal of Lagos State University, Faculty of Communication ad Media Studies</p>\r\n<p>(LASUSOC), Lagos, Nigeria. MCR is a peer-reviewed, scholarly journal of LASU School of Communication, aimed at promoting the development of theory and practice of media and communication in all remifications. Towards the realisation of the objectives for the establishment MCR, we now invite you to submit your original research reports for publication in our next edition.</p>\r\n<p>Submission details are as follows:</p>\r\n<p><strong>Paper Submission:&nbsp; &nbsp; </strong>April 30 (for June Edition)</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 160px;\">October 30 (for December Edition)</p>', '<p><strong>VISION</strong><br>To be a global journal, with critical, yet creative, problem-solving approach to scholarship and professionalism in al aspects of media and communication. The journal is aimed at promoting the development of theory and practice of media and communication in all ramifications</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>MISSION STATEMENT</strong><br>Media and Communication Review (MCR) is in furtherance of one of the objectives for the establishment of Lagos State University (LASU) &ldquo;to promote, by research and other means, the advancement of knowledge and its practical application in social, cultural, economic, scientific and technological problems&rdquo; in the society. Accordingly, MCR is committed to providing the forum for solid collaboration between academics and professionals for the advancement of research and application in all area of media and communication including: Journalism, Broadcasting, Advertising, Public Relations, Book Publishing, Film/Video, Photography, Interpersonal Communication, Cross-cultural/Global Communication, Information Communication Technology (ICT) and other emerging media. The Journal publishes cutting edge research articles that promote sound theoretical understanding and critical analysis of contemporary issues that advance societal development and promote highest standard of scholarship and professionalism in media and communication.</p>\r\n<p><strong>SCOPE</strong><br>Contribution are welcome in any of the following areas: Journalism,&nbsp;Broadcasting, Advertising, Public Relations, Book Publishing,&nbsp;Film/Video, Photography, Interpersonal Communication, Crosscultural/Global Communication, Information Communication</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p class=\"p1\"><strong>MEDIA AND </strong><strong style=\"font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, \'Open Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', sans-serif;\">COMMUNICATION REVIEW</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\">Journal of the Faculty of Communication and Media Studies, Lagos State University</p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"p4\"><strong>Editor-in-Chief:</strong> Professor Sunday Olayinka Alawode, PhD</p>\r\n<p class=\"p4\"><strong>Editor: </strong>Professor Jide Jimoh, PhD</p>\r\n<p class=\"p4\"><strong>Editor</strong> (Online Version):Jimi Kayode, PhD</p>\r\n<p class=\"p4\"><strong>Deputy Editor</strong> (Print Version): Toyosi O.S. Owolabi, PhD</p>\r\n<p class=\"p4\"><strong>Deputy Editor</strong> (Online Version): Tunde Akanni, PhD</p>\r\n<p class=\"p4\"><strong>Business Manager</strong>: Noeem Taiwo Thanny</p>\r\n<p class=\"p4\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"p4\"><strong>International Editorial Advisory Board&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Professor Idowu Sobowale</strong>, Ph.D., Department of Mass Communication, Covenant&nbsp;University, Ota, Nigeria.<br><strong>Professor Ralph Akinfeleye</strong>, Ph.D., Professor of Mass Communication and&nbsp;Chairman, Department of Mass Communication, University of Lagos, Nigeria.<br><strong>Professor Umaru Pate</strong>, Ph.D., Head, Department of Mass Communication, Bayero University, Kano, Nigeria.<br><strong>Professor Andrew Moemeka</strong>, Ph.D., Department of Mass Communication,&nbsp;Covenant University, Ota, Nigeria.<br><strong>Professor Rotimi Williams Olatunji,</strong> Department of Public Relations and Advertising, Lagos State University, Ojo, Lagos.<br><strong>Professor Stella Okunna</strong>, Ph.D., Nnamdi Azikiwe University, Awka, Nigeria.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>UNITED STATES OF AMERICA</strong><br><strong>Professor Anthony Olorunisola</strong>, Ph.D., Professor of Film and Media Studies, Penn State University, United States of America<br><strong>Professor Matt Mogekwu</strong>, Journalism Department, Roy H. Park School of Communications, Ithaca, NY 14850, USA, Tel: (607) 274 1994; (301) 651 5430<br><strong>Professor Bala A. Musa</strong>, PhD, Head, Department of Mass Communication and Chair Azusa Pacific University, 901 East Alosta Ave., Azusa, CA 91702</p>\r\n<p><strong>UNITED KINGDOM</strong><br><strong>Dr. Kaitynn Mende,</strong> University of Leicester, United Kingdom<br><strong>Dr. Ayo Oyeleye</strong>, Senior Lecturer, Media Studies; Programme Director, Postgraduate Media Programmes Birmingham, School of Media, Brimingham City University, Birmingham</p>\r\n<p><strong>INDIA</strong><br><strong>Professor Raji Ravi</strong>, Department of Mass Communication, Bangalore University,&nbsp;Bangalore, India.</p>\r\n<p><strong>SOUTH AFRICA</strong><br><strong>Professor Salawu Abiodun</strong>, PhD, Department of Communication, North West University, Mafikeng Campus, Private Mail Bag X 2046, Mbabatho 2735, South&nbsp;Africa</p>', '<h3><strong>Manuscripts Submission Guidelines</strong></h3>\r\n<h4><strong>1. Originality and Contribution:</strong></h4>\r\n<p>Any article submitted to Media and Communication Review (MCR) should be the original unpublished work of the author(s) and exclusive to this journal. Articles should provide a significant contribution to knowledge in the field of media and communication, with emphasis on areas such as Journalism, Broadcasting, Advertising, Public Relations, Book Publishing, Film/Video, Photography, Interpersonal Communication, Cross-cultural/Global Communication, Information Communication Technology (ICT), and emerging media.&nbsp;MCR also addresses contemporary issues and practices related to stakeholders in media and communication professionals, organizations, regulatory institutions, and actors in the public sphere.</p>\r\n<h4>2. Types of Manuscripts:</h4>\r\n<p>The journal accepts theoretical, empirical, methodological, and/or philosophical manuscripts. Manuscripts addressing conceptual issues, application articles/case studies, book reviews, video/film reviews, and other critical reviews are particularly welcome.</p>\r\n<h4>3. Selection and Responsibility:</h4>\r\n<p>The editors are responsible for the selection and acceptance of manuscripts.<br>Authors have the sole responsibility for the statements expressed and accuracy of facts within their manuscripts.<br>Authors are expected to review and return proofs within specified deadlines.</p>\r\n<h4>4. Manuscript Length and Elements:</h4>\r\n<p>Manuscripts should ideally range from 5,000 to 6,000 words, excluding tables and exhibits.<br>All tables should be included at the end of the paper as an appendix.<br>Authors have flexibility in including various elements such as text, tables, graphics, animation, or audio components to enhance their article.</p>\r\n<h4>5. Submission Process:</h4>\r\n<p>Visit our MCR journal host website using this link: [insert link]<br>Create an account by filling in the required details and clicking \"register.\"<br>Verify your account by checking your email for a code from info@researchafricapublications.com. If not found in your inbox, please check your spam folder and mark it as \"not spam.\"<br>To submit a paper, log in to your created account, click \"VIEW PROFILE,\" select \"Create Article,\" fill in all necessary information, attach the article, and click \"Submit.\"</p>\r\n<h4>6. Blind Peer Review:</h4>\r\n<p>To ensure an effective blind peer review process, please exclude any personal identifiable details from the title page of your submission.<br>Do not include the author\'s name, address, institutional affiliation, email address, telephone number(s), or any other identifying information on the title page.</p>\r\n<h4>7. References:</h4>\r\n<p>MCR, the blind peer-reviewed journal, follows the latest American Psychological Association (APA) format for its references</p>', '<p>Open Access</p>', 26, '2488-0014', '2488-0014', NULL);
