(12, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">More than ten years ago, Herbert Gans argued that the general public is impacted by the choices and deeds of powerful politicians and other members of the political elite who serve as the primary sources of news. Unexpectedly, when it comes to issues affecting regular people, traditional news reports appear to mute their voices. This study notes, from preliminary investigation that news reports on Tradermoni money poverty reduction programme are not multiperspectival which has led to Nigerians to take to air their voices on Twitter, the evolving digital public sphere. Based on theory of social construction and using Norman Fairclough Critical Discourse Analysis approach, this research sets out to critically analyse twitter conversations on Tradermoni poverty programme in Nigeria. Findings from this will fill the gap in existing knowledge</p>', '1', 8, NULL, '2023-06-13 00:41:54', '2023-06-13 00:50:20', NULL),
