(16, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; margin: 0cm 54.4pt .0001pt 35.45pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Avenir Book\';\">Herbert Gans asserted over ten years ago that the decisions and actions of high government officials and the rest of the political elites who are the main sources of news affect regular people. Interestingly, in matters that affects the ordinary people, their voices are seemingly silenced in news report. This study, therefore, sets out to verify the veracity of the claim that journalists are not as multiperspectival in news reports. Authenticating this claim is significant effort towards understanding social production of news. Based on theory of social construction of the news, and using content analysis, this study investigates the main sources of news reports in Tradermoni poverty reduction programme in selected Nigerian newspapers to examine the issues of news source bias.</span></p>', '2', 9, NULL, '2023-06-13 13:38:39', '2023-06-13 13:39:47', NULL),
