f respondents perceived that</span><span class=\"s7\"> newspapers\'</span><span class=\"s7\"> reportage</span><span class=\"s7\"> of</span><span class=\"s7\">the</span><span class=\"s7\"> conicts</span><span class=\"s7\"> were</span><span class=\"s7\"> capable</span><span class=\"s7\"> of</span><span class=\"s7\"> escalating conict.</span><span class=\"s7\"> The</span><span class=\"s7\"> paper</span><span class=\"s7\"> concludes</span><span class=\"s7\"> that</span><span class=\"s7\">achieving</span><span class=\"s7\"> peaceful</span><span class=\"s7\"> coexistence</span><span class=\"s7\"> and security</span> <span class=\"s7\">of</span> <span class=\"s7\">the</span> <span class=\"s7\">people</span> <span class=\"s7\">in</span> <span class=\"s7\">contemporary</span><span class=\"s7\">Nigeria</span> <span class=\"s7\">is</span> <span class=\"s7\">possible</span> <span class=\"s7\">when</span> <span class=\"s7\">there</span> <span class=\"s7\">is</span> <span class=\"s7\">an effective</span><span class=\"s7\"> communication</span><span class=\"s7\"> process,</span><span class=\"s7\"> and</span><span class=\"s7\">recommends</span><span class=\"s7\"> that</span><span class=\"s7\"> journalists</span><span class=\"s7\"> and media houses should avoid circulating news items capable of escalating </span><span class=\"s7\">conicts.</span></p>', '10', 67, 19, '2023-11-08 21:24:18', '2023-11-08 21:32:06', NULL),
(83, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 150%;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',\'serif\';\">Abstract</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt; text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',\'serif\';\">In the digital era of cheap hand-held devices, cable systems, streaming platforms, <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span>affordable internet tariffs occasioned by the Global System of Mobile telecommunications (GSM), increased sale of second TV sets and credit facilities to purchase new TV sets, watching television has not only become a popular culture, but also that the number of people with access to television programmes has increased. Brands are seizing this opportunity to popularise their products, retain existing customers and win converts with persuasive TV commercials. This study was carried out to investigate </span><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',\'serif\'; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;\">the level of awareness and, the influence of sports betting television advertisements on the betting habit of sports enthusiasts in Ibadan metropolis, south west Nigeria. Methodologically, survey research design was adopted, with a structured questionnaire as the instrument of research. Out of the five urban local councils in Ibadan, and using Purposive Sampling technique, Ibadan North-West local government, Onireke, was chosen because of its multicultural nature. Using the online sample calculator, 300 respondents were sampled out of the 216, 000 projected population of the council inhabitants. Purposively, copies of questionnaire were administered on individuals who patronised football viewing centres and sports betting centres for the study. The study was based on the Game Theory. Findings indicate 92.5% level of awareness of sports betting TV advertisements of popular brands. Further, influence of sports betting TV advertisements on bettors, to engage in betting stood at 80%. Moreover, bettors averred that advertisements on television about sports betting portrayed betting as a risk-free way of making money (1.39&plusmn;0.60) and sports betting activity as a normal and enjoyable pastime by actors in television advertisements (1.33&plusmn;0.53). The study concludes that, sports betting brands that wish to remain in the cognizance of sports enthusiasts and potential bettors for patronage cannot ignore television advertisements in this contemporary time. It is recommended that, individuals should endeavour to interpret the contents of advertisements and relate it to the existing realities that it is a game of chance, and not risk-free. Governments should also put in place, policies that will make it compulsory for betting companies to include warnings against the dangers of gambling in TV commercials to protect the unsuspecting members of the society.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',\'serif\';\">&nbsp;</span></p>', '2', 68, NULL, '2023-11-12 14:34:26', '2024-03-06 23:21:16', NULL),
